question: Consider the average difference between K-12 enrollment and 15-17 enrollment of schools that are locally funded, list the names and DOC type of schools which has a difference above this average.
SQL:
WITH enrollment_difference AS (
    SELECT 
        s."School",
        s."DOCType",
        (f."Enrollment (K-12)" - f."Enrollment (Ages 5-17)") AS enrollment_diff
    FROM 
        public.frpm f
    JOIN 
        public.schools s ON f."CDSCode" = s."CDSCode"
    WHERE 
        s."FundingType" = 'Locally Funded'
),
average_difference AS (
    SELECT 
        AVG(enrollment_diff) AS avg_diff
    FROM 
        enrollment_difference
)
SELECT 
    ed."School",
    ed."DOCType"
FROM 
    enrollment_difference ed,
    average_difference ad
WHERE 
    ed.enrollment_diff > ad.avg_diff;
